USE CASE 1: Generate Country Population Report
CHARACTERISTIC INFORMATION
Goal in Context
Show a list of all countries sorted by population (largest to smallest) and let the user download it.

Scope
Population Reporting System (the app that makes these reports).

Level
Primary task

Preconditions
The database is up and reachable.
Country population data exists.
The user can access the app.

Success End Condition
The user sees a country list sorted by population and can download it.

Failed End Condition
No report is shown; the user sees a clear error message.

Primary Actor
User / Analyst

Trigger
The user clicks “Country Population Report”.

MAIN SUCCESS SCENARIO
Open the app.
Choose “Country Population Report”.
The app checks the request.
The app reads country data from the database.
The app sorts countries by population (largest first).
The app shows the results in a table.
The user downloads the file (CSV/Excel/PDF).
The app saves the run to history.
action description
Columns: Code, Name, Continent, Region, Population, Capital.
Sorting is strictly by population, largest first.

EXTENSIONS
Input issue → The app shows what to fix.
Database issue → The app shows “service temporarily unavailable”.
No data → The app shows “No countries found”.
Export issue → The app asks the user to try another format or retry.

SUB-VARIATIONS
Optional filters: by continent or region.
Export formats: CSV, Excel, PDF.
Page size: 25, 50, or 100 rows.

SCHEDULE
DUE DATE: Oct 31, 2025


USE CASE 2: Generate Top N Populated Cities Report
CHARACTERISTIC INFORMATION
Goal in Context
Let the user see the Top N cities by population for a chosen scope (world, continent, region, country, or district), and download it.

Scope
Population Reporting System.

Level
Primary task

Preconditions
City population data exists and links to country/region/continent/district.
The user can access the app.
A valid N is provided (e.g., 1–500).

Success End Condition
The user sees the Top N cities for the chosen scope and can download the file.

Failed End Condition
No report is shown; the user sees why (bad N or scope, or no results).

Primary Actor
User / Analyst

Trigger
The user clicks “Top N Cities” and enters N (and optional scope).

MAIN SUCCESS SCENARIO
Open the app.
Choose “Top N Cities”.
Enter N and (optionally) pick a scope.
The app validates N and scope.
The app reads city data for the scope.
The app sorts by population and keeps the first N.
The app shows the results (Name, Country, District, Population).
The user downloads the file (CSV/Excel/PDF).
The app saves the run to history.
action description
Default N = 10; maximum N = 500 (configurable).
Stable sort: Population (desc), then Name (A–Z).

EXTENSIONS
Invalid N → The app asks for a valid number.
Unknown scope → The app suggests valid values.
No matches → The app suggests changing filters.
Export issue → The app offers another format or retry.

SUB-VARIATIONS
Scope: world, continent, region, country, district.
Optional columns: add latitude/longitude if available.
Secondary sort: Name (A–Z).

SCHEDULE
DUE DATE: Nov 1, 2025

USE CASE 3: Generate Language Population Report
CHARACTERISTIC INFORMATION
Goal in Context
Show how many people speak Chinese, English, Hindi, Spanish, and Arabic, plus each one’s percentage of the world population.

Scope
Population Reporting System.

Level
Primary task

Preconditions
Language speaker data can be calculated from country data.
World total population is available.
The user can access the app.

Success End Condition
The user sees a table with total speakers and % of world for each language and can download it.

Failed End Condition
No report is shown; the user sees a helpful error.

Primary Actor
User / Analyst

Trigger
The user clicks “Language Population Report”.

MAIN SUCCESS SCENARIO
Open the app.
Choose “Language Population Report”.
The app checks that the world total is available.
The app adds up speakers for each language across countries.
The app computes % of world = speakers / world_total × 100.
The app shows the results (Language, Total Speakers, % of World).
The user downloads the file (CSV/Excel/PDF).
The app saves the run to history.
action description
Percentages are rounded to 2 decimals (can be changed).
If data is missing for a language, show “Data not available”.

EXTENSIONS
World total missing → The app stops and explains the issue.
Language data missing → The app shows “Data not available” for that language but completes the rest.
Export issue → The app offers another format or retry.

SUB-VARIATIONS
Admins can add or remove languages.
Order by speakers (default) or alphabetically.
Percentage precision: 1–3 decimals.

SCHEDULE
DUE DATE: Nov 3, 2025
